'''薇拉·凯瑟'''（{{lang-en|'''Willa Cather'''}}，{{bd|1873年|12月7日|1947年|4月24日|catIdx=Cather}}<ref>Woodress, James Leslie. ''Willa Cather: A Literary Life'', Omaha, NE: University of Nebraska Press, 1987, p. 516. Cather's birth date is confirmed by a birth certificate and a January 22, 1874 letter of her father's referring to her. While working at ''[[McClure's|McClure's Magazine]]'', Cather claimed to be born in 1875. After 1920, she claimed 1876 as her birth year. That is the date carved into her gravestone at [[Jaffrey,_New_Hampshire|Jaffrey, New Hampshire]].</ref>），[[美國|美國]]作家，以"One of Ours"一書，於1923年得到[[普立茲獎|普立茲獎]]，作品以擅長描寫女性及美國早期移民的拓荒開墾生活而聞名（著作如《哦·拓荒者！》及《我的安東妮亞》)，為美國重要的鄉土作者之一。她在[[内布拉斯加州|内布拉斯加州]]长大，毕业于内布拉斯加大学。在[[匹兹堡|匹兹堡]]生活和工作了十年，然后在她33岁时搬到了[[纽约|纽约]]，在那里度过了余生。

==生平==
[[File:Willa_Cather_house_from_NE_3.JPG|250px]]
薇拉·凯瑟生於[[維吉尼亞州|維吉尼亞州]][[溫徹斯特_(維吉尼亞州)|溫徹斯特]]，9岁时隨家人移居[[内布拉斯加州|内布拉斯加州]]，薇拉有六个弟妹：Roscoe，Douglass，Jessica，James，John和Elsie。<ref>Lewis, Edith. ''Willa Cather Living: A Personal Record'', New York: Alfred Knopf, 1953, pp. 5–7.</ref>根据薇拉的传记作者Hermione Lee描述，薇拉与弟弟关系很好，与妹妹关系不十分亲密。<ref>Lee, Hermione. ''Willa Cather: Double Lives''. New York: Pantheon, 1989, p. 36.</ref>在女性長輩的財務支持下，她毕业于内布拉斯加大学，成為當時少數擁有大學學歷的女性之一，她熱愛寫作，學生時期常在Nebraska State Journal發表文章<ref>Woodress, James, pp. 72–3.</ref>，大學畢業後當過高中教師及 McClure's 雜誌社總編輯。

她於1906年由内布拉斯加遷至紐約，任職於 McClure's 雜誌社，1908年升為總編輯，於業餘寫作，並擁有多位文壇上的好友。她的第一本著作為 "Alexander's Bridge" ，文風深受[[亨利·詹姆斯|亨利·詹姆斯]]影響，後認識作家Sarah Orne Jewett，建議她改變寫作方向，多描述自己的故鄉内布拉斯加，她因而回到故鄉尋找寫作靈感，而那些著作(My Antonia 及 O! Pioneers!)使她深受文藝評論及讀者歡迎。

==个人生活==
19世纪90年代初薇拉·凯瑟作为一名学生在内布拉斯加大学时，有着男性化的绰号“威廉”，喜欢穿着男性化的服装。<ref>O'Brien, Sharon. ''Willa Cather: The Emerging Voice''. New York: Oxford, 1987. pp. 96–113.</ref>内布拉斯加大学的档案照片中显示凯瑟穿得像一个年轻的男子。<ref>Lewis, Edith. ''Willa Cather Living: A Personal Record'', p. 38. New York: Alfred Knopf, 1953</ref>

凯瑟終生未婚，因與數位女性過從甚密<ref>Rolfe, Lionel. (2004). ''The Uncommon Friendship of Yaltah Menuhin & Willa Cather''. American Legends/California Classics Books, 168 pp. ISBN 1-879395-46-0.</ref>，且在紐約工作時與女性同事共居一屋<ref>[http://cather.unl.edu "Cather's Life: Chronology"] {{Wayback|url=http://cather.unl.edu/ |date=20110518024433 }}, The Willa Cather Archive, University of Nebraska, accessed March 21, 2007</ref>，故曾被質疑為[[女同性戀|女同性戀]]者，但她否認。由於平日來往的書信已在死前被她焚毀，雖有少數保存在美國大學圖書館的書信留傳下來，但她在遺書中言明不許對外公開生平書信內容，因而學界至今遲遲還未能證明她的真實性向。

1947年4月24日凯瑟在纽约由于脑出血而死亡，被埋葬在[[新罕布什尔州|新罕布什尔州]]Jaffrey的一处墓地内。<ref>{{cite news |title=Willa Cather, Novelist, Dies Of Stroke At 70 |url=http://pqasb.pqarchiver.com/chicagotribune/access/473858882.html?dids=473858882:473858882&FMT=ABS&FMTS=ABS:AI&type=historic&date=Apr+25%2C+1947&author=&pub=Chicago+Tribune&desc=WILLA+CATHER%2C+NOVELIST%2C+DIES+OF+STROKE+AT+70&pqatl=google |quote=Willa Cather, one of America's foremost novelists and short story writers died here today, reportedly of a cerebral hemorrhage. Miss Cather, who had ... |work=Chicago Tribune |date=1947-04-25 |accessdate=2009-12-10 |archive-date=2012-11-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121103122934/http://pqasb.pqarchiver.com/chicagotribune/access/473858882.html?dids=473858882:473858882&FMT=ABS&FMTS=ABS:AI&type=historic&date=Apr+25,+1947&author=&pub=Chicago+Tribune&desc=WILLA+CATHER,+NOVELIST,+DIES+OF+STROKE+AT+70&pqatl=google |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Willa Cather, Novelist, Dies At 70 Received Pulitzer Prize In 1922 |url=http://pqasb.pqarchiver.com/courant/access/903401822.html?dids=903401822:903401822&FMT=ABS&FMTS=ABS:AI&type=historic&date=Apr+25%2C+1947&author=&pub=Hartford+Courant&desc=Willa+Cather%2C+Novelist%2C+Dies+At+70+Received+Pulitzer+Prize+In+1922&pqatl=google |quote=Willa Cather, 70, one of the Nation's foremost novelists, died here today. |work=[[Associated_Press|Associated Press]] in the [[Hartford_Courant|Hartford Courant]] |date=1947-04-25 |accessdate=2009-12-10 |archive-date=2012-11-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121103122949/http://pqasb.pqarchiver.com/courant/access/903401822.html?dids=903401822:903401822&FMT=ABS&FMTS=ABS:AI&type=historic&date=Apr+25,+1947&author=&pub=Hartford+Courant&desc=Willa+Cather,+Novelist,+Dies+At+70+Received+Pulitzer+Prize+In+1922&pqatl=google |dead-url=no }}</ref>

